x4freetext: *By authors*.The production cross sections are
calculated by applying several corrections-
the measured dead-time of the data-acquisition
system, the efficiency of the detection system, the
correction for non-fully stripped ions, correction for
secondary reactions in the FRS beam line, correction
for angular transmission, correction for secondary
reactions inside the target.
the systematic error on the production cross
sections due to uncertainties of all the above
mentioned corrections was estimated to Be 15% for all
fission fragments. For spallation residues a final
systematic error ranging from of 9% for lead to 25%
for promethium was estimated.
